    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1480"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/95.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Edwards</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>International interest displayed in details connected with Benton matter makes it
                    necessary that you telegraph all obtainable facts. Department desires to know
                    especially the form of encounter which took place in Villa’s room, and if
                    witnesses were present the name of each. Did Benton draw a gun and threaten to
                    shoot Villa? What was the physical condition of Benton when he was removed from
                    the presence of Villa? Who removed him? Where was he taken? Give facts about the
                    trial and execution. Secure written statements from all witnesses whose
                    testimony would be valuable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
